<p><b>Information retrieval</b> is the activity of obtaining information resources relevant to an information need from a collection of information resources. Searches can be based on <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metadata" title="Metadata">metadata</a> or on full-text (or other content-based) indexing.</p>
<p>Automated information retrieval systems are used to reduce what has been called "<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Information_overload" title="Information overload">information overload</a>". Many universities and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Public_library" title="Public library">public libraries</a> use IR systems to provide access to books, journals and other documents. <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_search_engine" title="Web search engine">Web search engines</a> are the most visible <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Information_retrieval_applications" title="Information retrieval applications">IR applications</a>.</p>
<p></p>
